The paper discusses network optimization in wireless communication systems, which falls under the category of computer science - networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The proposed framework utilizes machine learning techniques, which suggests the paper could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of reinforcement learning (RL) also suggests the paper could be categorized under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the reduction of computation complexity, which could also place it under information theory (cs.IT).
